From the results above, I have realised that

a. HashSet is the fastest collection in terms of Iterations operations.
b. LinkedList is the fastest in terms of Insertions.
c. TreeSet is the fastest in terms of Lookup operations.

--------------------------------------------------------------
The optimal structure for a 'recently viewed products' feature:

I'd go for a LinkedList: it remembers the sequence. When you iterate through a LinkedHashSet, you are guaranteed to get the items back in the exact order they were added.
Hence, it will easily allow you to implement a 'recently viewed products' feature, more efficiently.

